# IntelliJ HTTP Client examples for technical-interview-demo
# Localization writes require ADMIN and an authenticated session.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@sessionCookie = paste-technical-interview-demo-session-here
@localizationId = 1
@writeLocalizationId = 0
@demoMessageKey = info.book.created.demo-change-me-if-rerunning

### LocalizationController - list localizations with pagination and sorting
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/localizations?page=0&size=5&sort=messageKey,asc&sort=language,asc
Accept: application/json

### LocalizationController - filter localizations by key and language and capture the first id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/localizations?messageKey=error.book.not_found&language=en
Accept: application/json

> {%
if (response.status === 200 && response.body.content.length > 0) {
  client.global.set("localizationId", String(response.body.content[0].id));
}
%}

### LocalizationController - get localization message by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/localizations/{{localizationId}}
Accept: application/json

### LocalizationController - list messages for one language
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/localizations?language=es&sort=messageKey,asc
Accept: application/json

### LocalizationController - create localization (ADMIN + authenticated session)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/localizations
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "messageKey": "{{demoMessageKey}}",
  "language": "fr",
  "messageText": "Le livre a ete cree.",
  "description": "French success message for demo requests."
}
> {%
if (response.status === 201) {
  client.global.set("writeLocalizationId", String(response.body.id));
}
%}

### LocalizationController - update the localization message created above (run create first)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/localizations/{{writeLocalizationId}}
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "messageKey": "{{demoMessageKey}}",
  "language": "fr",
  "messageText": "Le livre a ete cree avec succes.",
  "description": "Updated French success message for demo requests."
}

### LocalizationController - delete the localization created above (run create first)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/localizations/{{writeLocalizationId}}
Cookie: technical-interview-demo-session={{sessionCookie}}
